</h3><p class="sc-iLLNPL dGtRC pf-51_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the UK, various statutory and regulatory requirements impact CPR training, particularly within healthcare and childcare settings:


















</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dISoPS kgxkyr pf-53_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-54_ pf-text-1">The Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981 mandate that employers, including those in healthcare and education, provide adequate and appropriate equipment and facilities for rendering first aid.






























</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-56_ pf-text-1">The Care Quality Commission (CQC) outlines that healthcare providers must have staff trained in CPR to comply with health and safety standards.






























</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-58_ pf-text-1">Organisations must also adhere to the guidelines set by the Resuscitation Council UK, regularly updated in line with international research and best practices.































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-60_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-djTQOc gLxCly pf-61_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bhqpXc bptxD pf-62_ pf-heading-1-h3">Understanding CPR guidelines for children
